<div class="basictext">

<h4>Welcome to LAMP, the electronic music library at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.</h4><p>

<center>
<table width="80%"><tr><td width="30%" id="bighspace"><div class="playlist_box"><b>The Library Access to Music Project has ended.</b></div><P>

[October 11, 2016] LAMP closes after 15 years of the project, and 12 years after the library opened in October 2004. More than 4,100 distinct
members of the MIT community served as "DJs" during that time, playing about 90 songs each day for the last 12 years. SIPB hosted a
party on campus to commemorate the end of the project.<p>

<iframe width="280" height="158" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/WbEjhNfwKBA" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

<p>

[April 25, 2009] LAMP is up to 1,915 CDs. <p>

[March 27, 2009] LAMP is now in stereo.

<P>Please send questions,
comments, and bug reports to <a
href="mailto:lamp@mit.edu">lamp@mit.edu</a>.<P>

